Every scholar and scientist was to some degree or in some sense working on the problem, which was generally agreed to be metabolic and probably dietary. There was of course nothing wrong with the emperor‚Äôs diet, but it was assumed that some adjustment (possibly quite infinitesimal) would turn the trick and give His Highness relief. This time (that look told them) something uncomfortably new was in the offing.‚Äù ‚ÄúThe Prime Minister‚Äôs announcement (that the cause of the Imperial Chill had been found) was shockingly brief‚Äîand was followed by a shocked silence, which soon became a murmur of horror, disbelief, and denial. What outraged them was the idea that, after defeating the best minds of a dozen generations, the Emperor‚Äôs chilliness could be explained so simply.
